In [14]:
#scatter chart
plt.scatter(cars_data['Age'],cars_data['Price'],c='red')
plt.title("Scatter plot of price vs Age")
plt.xlabel("Age(months)")
plt.ylabel("Price(euros)")
plt.show()
plt.scatter(cars_data['HP'],cars_data['Price'],c='green')
plt.title("Scatter plot of price vs HP")
plt.xlabel("HP")
plt.ylabel("Price(euros)")
plt.show()
plt.scatter(cars_data['Weight'],cars_data['Price'],c='black')
plt.title("Scatter plot of price vs weight")
plt.xlabel("weight(kg)")
plt.ylabel("Price(euros)")
plt.show()

In [44]:
#barplot
#cars_data['FuelType'].value_counts()
counts=[1277,144,15] #unique numerical values of fueltype
value=['petrol','diesel','CNG']#np.unique(cars_data['FuelType']) #storing unique values of fueltype
index=np.arange(len(value))
plt.bar(index,counts,color=['red','blue','cyan'])
plt.title('Bargraph of fueltype')
plt.xlabel('fueltype')
plt.ylabel('frequency')
plt.xticks(index,value,rotation=90)
plt.show()
